Acute nonhemodynamic pulmonary edema with nifedipine in primary pulmonary hypertension.
 A 34-year-old man with primary pulmonary hypertension developed acute nonhemodynamic pulmonary edema after a loading dose of nifedipine.
 Changes of the vascular permeability induced by the drug acting on the arteriolar wall of the capillary system could be an explanation.
